('proj-local-model-demo', 'ph-model-providers-open-source', 91, 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Optional Local Model Demo', 'Optional practice project: Run an open model locally or on a hosted server and compare quality, cost, latency, and operational tradeoffs.', 'This project gives learners a concrete way to practice Model APIs, Providers, and Open Source Models by producing a working Local Model Demo notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes. The artifact is intended for review and reflection, not as proof of mastery or job readiness.', 'side', 'ph-model-providers-open-source-projects', 9, 91, 10, 'intermediate', 35, 280, 12870, '{"project":true,"projectBrief":"Run an open model locally or on a hosted server and compare quality, cost, latency, and operational tradeoffs.","projectKind":"ai_ml_application","projectScope":"small_practice_artifact","projectPurpose":"Practice the surrounding roadmap segment through a small reviewable artifact.","phaseContext":"Model APIs, Providers, and Open Source Models","deliverable":"a working Local Model Demo notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes","skillsToPractice":["Model APIs, Providers, and Open Source Models"],"suggestedSteps":["Define the Local Model Demo scenario and list the specific items to demonstrate: model behavior and evaluation.","Choose the dataset, model, prompt, retrieval source, or tool boundary required by the project brief.","Build the baseline workflow first, then add the AI/ML behavior in a way that can be inspected.","Capture evaluation cases that include successful output, weak output, and at least one failure mode.","Add safeguards, citations, metrics, traces, or manual review notes where the project context requires them.","Document model assumptions, limitations, cost/latency concerns, and what would need review before real use."],"expectedEvidence":["a working Local Model Demo notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes.","README or notes that explain setup, usage, assumptions, and expected output.","Evaluation cases, model/prompt/retrieval configuration, and notes on weak or unsafe outputs.","Validation evidence such as tests, screenshots, logs, query results, metrics, traces, or review notes.","Short reflection on trade-offs, limitations, and one reasonable next improvement."],"reviewFocus":["Does the artifact directly match the project brief?","Can another person run, inspect, or review the result from the provided notes?","Are assumptions, limitations, and trade-offs stated clearly?"],"scopeGuardrails":["Keep the implementation focused on the stated project brief.","Prefer a complete small artifact over a broad unfinished system.","Treat completion as reviewable evidence, not a certification claim."],"claimLimit":"Completion creates reviewable project evidence. It does not certify mastery or guarantee job readiness.","evidenceRequired":true,"optionalPractice":true,"milestone":false,"source":"roadmap.sh/ai-engineer","nodeKey":"proj-local-model-demo"}'::jsonb, false, true, '["Apply Model APIs, Providers, and Open Source Models through a focused Local Model Demo artifact.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a working Local Model Demo notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes is available for review.","The Local Model Demo scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness."]'::jsonb),
('chk-model-selection-review', 'ph-model-providers-open-source', 99, 'checkpoint', 'review', NULL, NULL, 'Model Selection Review', 'Review checkpoint for Model APIs, Providers, and Open Source Models. The learner synthesizes completed topics such as OpenAI Platform, Anthropic Claude, Google Gemini, Azure AI Foundry, records evidence, and updates the learning plan before continuing.', 'This checkpoint turns the phase boundary into a reflection and evidence-review step for the AI engineering roadmap rather than another unchecked content topic.', 'checkpoint', 'ph-model-providers-open-source-checkpoints', 9, 99, 2, 'intermediate', 65, 280, 13590, '{"checkpoint": true, "source": "roadmap.sh/ai-engineer", "nodeKey": "chk-model-selection-review", "checkpointPurpose": "phase_review", "reviewMode": "review", "evidenceRequired": true, "claimLimit": "orientation_and_progress_review_only_not_certification"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Explain how topics from Model APIs, Providers, and Open Source Models connect to realistic AI engineering work.", "Select evidence that shows attempted practice, reasoning, or implementation decisions.", "Identify which topics need review before moving to later roadmap areas."]'::jsonb, '["Write a concise review of the main ideas from this segment.", "Include one evidence artifact such as notes, a diagram, lab output, code, query results, screenshots, or a project review.", "Record open questions, weak areas, or follow-up actions.", "Mark the checkpoint complete only after the review artifact and next steps are captured."]'::jsonb),
