('proj-deploy-ai-api', 'ph-infra-deployment-observability', 91, 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Optional Deployed AI API', 'Optional practice project: Deploy an AI API with Docker, CI/CD, rate limits, logs, metrics, and a simple dashboard.', 'This project gives learners a concrete way to practice AI Infrastructure, Deployment, and Observability by producing a working Deployed AI API notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes. The artifact is intended for review and reflection, not as proof of mastery or job readiness.', 'side', 'ph-infra-deployment-observability-projects', 12, 91, 12, 'advanced', 35, 280, 14430, '{"project":true,"projectBrief":"Deploy an AI API with Docker, CI/CD, rate limits, logs, metrics, and a simple dashboard.","projectKind":"ai_ml_application","projectScope":"small_practice_artifact","projectPurpose":"Practice the surrounding roadmap segment through a small reviewable artifact.","phaseContext":"AI Infrastructure, Deployment, and Observability","deliverable":"a working Deployed AI API notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes","skillsToPractice":["Observability"],"suggestedSteps":["Define the Deployed AI API scenario and list the specific items to demonstrate: API behavior, dashboard decisions, container setup, CI checks, deployment flow.","Choose the dataset, model, prompt, retrieval source, or tool boundary required by the project brief.","Build the baseline workflow first, then add the AI/ML behavior in a way that can be inspected.","Capture evaluation cases that include successful output, weak output, and at least one failure mode.","Add safeguards, citations, metrics, traces, or manual review notes where the project context requires them.","Document model assumptions, limitations, cost/latency concerns, and what would need review before real use."],"expectedEvidence":["a working Deployed AI API notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes.","README or notes that explain setup, usage, assumptions, and expected output.","Evaluation cases, model/prompt/retrieval configuration, and notes on weak or unsafe outputs.","Validation evidence such as tests, screenshots, logs, query results, metrics, traces, or review notes.","Short reflection on trade-offs, limitations, and one reasonable next improvement."],"reviewFocus":["Does the artifact directly match the project brief?","Can another person run, inspect, or review the result from the provided notes?","Are assumptions, limitations, and trade-offs stated clearly?"],"scopeGuardrails":["Keep the implementation focused on the stated project brief.","Prefer a complete small artifact over a broad unfinished system.","Treat completion as reviewable evidence, not a certification claim."],"claimLimit":"Completion creates reviewable project evidence. It does not certify mastery or guarantee job readiness.","evidenceRequired":true,"optionalPractice":true,"milestone":false,"source":"roadmap.sh/ai-engineer","nodeKey":"proj-deploy-ai-api"}'::jsonb, false, true, '["Apply Observability through a focused Deployed AI API artifact.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a working Deployed AI API notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes is available for review.","The Deployed AI API scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness."]'::jsonb),
('ms-required-deployed-ai-system', 'ph-infra-deployment-observability', 92, 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Required Deployed AI System', 'Capstone project: Deploy a production-style AI system with monitoring, tracing, cost controls, safety checks, and documented runbooks.', 'This project gives learners a concrete way to practice AI Infrastructure, Deployment, and Observability by producing a working Deployed AI System notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes. The artifact is intended for review and reflection, not as proof of mastery or job readiness.', 'side', 'ph-infra-deployment-observability-projects', 12, 92, 18, 'advanced', 70, 280, 14520, '{"project":true,"projectBrief":"Deploy a production-style AI system with monitoring, tracing, cost controls, safety checks, and documented runbooks.","projectKind":"ai_ml_application","projectScope":"portfolio_capstone","projectPurpose":"Integrate several roadmap areas into a portfolio-ready case study.","phaseContext":"AI Infrastructure, Deployment, and Observability","deliverable":"a working Deployed AI System notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes","skillsToPractice":["Observability"],"suggestedSteps":["Define the Deployed AI System scenario and list the specific items to demonstrate: monitoring signals.","Choose the dataset, model, prompt, retrieval source, or tool boundary required by the project brief.","Build the baseline workflow first, then add the AI/ML behavior in a way that can be inspected.","Capture evaluation cases that include successful output, weak output, and at least one failure mode.","Add safeguards, citations, metrics, traces, or manual review notes where the project context requires them.","Document model assumptions, limitations, cost/latency concerns, and what would need review before real use.","Create a review checklist that connects the artifact to the relevant skills and roadmap segment.","Write a limitation and risk section so the project is presented as reviewable evidence, not a certification claim.","Document how to run or review the Deployed AI System deliverable, including inputs, expected outputs, and known limitations."],"expectedEvidence":["a working Deployed AI System notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes.","README or notes that explain setup, usage, assumptions, and expected output.","Evaluation cases, model/prompt/retrieval configuration, and notes on weak or unsafe outputs.","Validation evidence such as tests, screenshots, logs, query results, metrics, traces, or review notes.","Short reflection on trade-offs, limitations, and one reasonable next improvement.","Architecture, review checklist, and limitation section suitable for portfolio discussion."],"reviewFocus":["Does the artifact directly match the project brief?","Can another person run, inspect, or review the result from the provided notes?","Are assumptions, limitations, and trade-offs stated clearly?"],"scopeGuardrails":["Keep the implementation focused on the stated project brief.","Prefer a complete small artifact over a broad unfinished system.","Treat completion as reviewable evidence, not a certification claim."],"claimLimit":"Completion creates reviewable project evidence. It does not certify mastery or guarantee job readiness.","evidenceRequired":true,"optionalPractice":false,"milestone":true,"source":"roadmap.sh/ai-engineer","nodeKey":"ms-required-deployed-ai-system"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Apply Observability through a focused Deployed AI System artifact.","Integrate multiple roadmap areas into one coherent case study rather than isolated exercises.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a working Deployed AI System notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes is available for review.","The Deployed AI System scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","The case study connects implementation decisions to relevant roadmap skills and explains why alternatives were not chosen.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness.","The project is packaged so a reviewer can understand the artifact without live mentoring."]'::jsonb),
('chk-production-readiness', 'ph-infra-deployment-observability', 99, 'checkpoint', 'gate', NULL, NULL, 'Production Readiness Review', 'Review checkpoint for AI Infrastructure, Deployment, and Observability. The learner consolidates evidence from Docker for AI Apps, Environment Configuration, CI/CD with GitHub Actions, Secrets Management, identifies unresolved prerequisite gaps, and decides whether to continue, review selected topics, or complete extra practice before the next roadmap segment.', 'This checkpoint acts as a transition gate for the AI engineering roadmap. It supports reflection and planning; it is not a certification, mastery test, or claim of job readiness.', 'checkpoint', 'ph-infra-deployment-observability-checkpoints', 12, 99, 2, 'advanced', 65, 280, 15150, '{"checkpoint": true, "source": "roadmap.sh/ai-engineer", "nodeKey": "chk-production-readiness", "checkpointPurpose": "phase_review", "reviewMode": "gate", "evidenceRequired": true, "claimLimit": "orientation_and_progress_review_only_not_certification"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Summarize the main concepts and decisions from AI Infrastructure, Deployment, and Observability in practical AI engineering terms.", "Identify prerequisite gaps, unclear topics, or risks that should be reviewed before moving forward.", "Create a short evidence artifact that links completed roadmap items to what was learned."]'::jsonb, '["List the roadmap items reviewed for this checkpoint.", "Provide one evidence artifact such as notes, a diagram, a lab result, code, queries, screenshots, or a project review.", "Record at least two gaps, risks, or follow-up actions, or explicitly state that no critical gaps were found.", "Use the result to choose one next step: continue, review selected topics, or complete extra practice."]'::jsonb),
